1
00:00:05,076 --> 00:00:08,713
In exchange for stopping
the eviction, the son

2
00:00:08,780 --> 00:00:10,915
had to help "tidy up" the messy gun deal.

3
00:00:11,950 --> 00:00:13,017
The son?

4
00:00:13,084 --> 00:00:14,018
We know him as…

5
00:00:14,786 --> 00:00:15,854
Mogi.

6
00:00:16,855 --> 00:00:18,957
<i>"Get rid of that family."</i>

7
00:00:19,023 --> 00:00:20,358
<i>It really has</i>…

8
00:00:21,126 --> 00:00:22,727
been a long time.

9
00:00:33,338 --> 00:00:34,739
FROM: YUKITERU MOGI
TO: MINORU TAGUSARI

10
00:00:45,783 --> 00:00:47,685
1995

11
00:00:47,752 --> 00:00:50,054
I'm looking for anyone
who witnessed this murder!

12
00:00:50,121 --> 00:00:52,223
It happened April 26th!

13
00:00:52,290 --> 00:00:54,826
I'm looking for someone
who witnessed this murder!

14
00:00:54,893 --> 00:00:57,128
It happened April 26th!

15
00:00:57,195 --> 00:00:59,664
I'm looking for someone
who witnessed this murder!

16
00:00:59,731 --> 00:01:02,267
-It happened April 26th!
-Please help us.

17
00:01:02,767 --> 00:01:03,668
Please help!

18
00:01:03,735 --> 00:01:05,270
Please help us!

19
00:01:05,837 --> 00:01:07,105
Please help!

20
00:01:11,876 --> 00:01:13,011
You're hungry, right?

21
00:01:16,948 --> 00:01:17,916
Eat up.

22
00:01:19,083 --> 00:01:20,251
Thank you for the meal.

23
00:01:20,318 --> 00:01:21,653
Thank you for the meal.

24
00:01:35,266 --> 00:01:38,469
It tastes the same as Mom's cooking.

25
00:01:56,888 --> 00:01:58,022
Minoru?

26
00:02:10,368 --> 00:02:13,438
I'M SORRY

27
00:02:24,015 --> 00:02:25,049
What about work?

28
00:02:37,328 --> 00:02:38,396
Makoto.

29
00:02:43,101 --> 00:02:44,302
Mogi is…

30
00:02:45,303 --> 00:02:47,839
The deceased is Yukiteru Mogi.

31
00:02:47,905 --> 00:02:50,842
Since an empty medicine bottle
was found at the scene,

32
00:02:50,908 --> 00:02:54,646
it's probable he died
from acute drug poisoning,

33
00:02:54,712 --> 00:02:56,414
due to an overdose.

34
00:03:29,047 --> 00:03:33,017
KARASHIMA

35
00:03:48,433 --> 00:03:49,801
Guess we'll wait here.

36
00:03:50,702 --> 00:03:52,470
Excuse me.

37
00:03:53,137 --> 00:03:55,506
Looking for the Karashimas?
They went out earlier.

38
00:03:55,573 --> 00:03:56,974
They had luggage with them.

39
00:03:59,110 --> 00:04:01,045
My name is Tagusari,
I'm from the Aoi Station.

40
00:04:01,112 --> 00:04:02,780
Could you help with our investigation?

41
00:04:20,898 --> 00:04:23,301
So Mr. Koike really was involved too.

42
00:04:25,136 --> 00:04:26,437
Mogi was…

43
00:04:27,638 --> 00:04:30,174
threatened by the factory manager
and Sasaoka

44
00:04:30,908 --> 00:04:32,410
into killing Mom and Dad.

45
00:04:34,912 --> 00:04:37,482
If Mr. Koike was involved
in the illicit manufacturing,

46
00:04:37,548 --> 00:04:39,751
he must have known about Mogi's crime.

47
00:04:42,987 --> 00:04:46,758
But, I don't think Mr. Koike will talk.

48
00:04:49,327 --> 00:04:51,896
We have no choice but to look
for Fumi and her husband.

49
00:04:58,970 --> 00:05:00,938
I have somewhere I need to stop by.

50
00:05:09,113 --> 00:05:09,981
Haruko.

51
00:05:10,481 --> 00:05:13,050
CHINESE RESTAURANT
FOR SALE

52
00:05:15,086 --> 00:05:16,788
Is Minoru okay?

53
00:05:20,992 --> 00:05:22,527
Of course not.

54
00:05:25,229 --> 00:05:27,198
He's taking time off from work.

55
00:05:30,134 --> 00:05:31,702
It might take some time.

56
00:05:35,506 --> 00:05:39,777
I never imagined this place
would end up like this.

57
00:05:48,653 --> 00:05:51,122
Kind of makes you want to eat there, huh?

58
00:05:56,227 --> 00:05:58,296
They didn't suspect foul play, right?

59
00:06:03,301 --> 00:06:06,204
So he really was preparing to die…

60
00:06:11,275 --> 00:06:14,479
Seems he was talking to his lawyer.

61
00:06:15,546 --> 00:06:17,682
He asked the lawyer to use the money

62
00:06:17,748 --> 00:06:20,718
from selling the restaurant
to get his mom into a nursing home.

63
00:06:22,587 --> 00:06:24,689
It was a lonely end.

64
00:06:25,756 --> 00:06:27,425
He didn't even have a funeral,

65
00:06:28,092 --> 00:06:30,428
and was only seen off by his mother.

66
00:06:31,863 --> 00:06:35,867
I went to offer my prayers,
but I couldn't bear to watch it.

67
00:06:39,070 --> 00:06:40,771
We spent 31 years…

68
00:06:42,507 --> 00:06:45,243
all for things to end up like this…

69
00:06:50,748 --> 00:06:52,717
It feels so foolish.

70
00:07:03,327 --> 00:07:05,129
Find that couple for me.

71
00:07:07,965 --> 00:07:09,901
I have a ton of questions to ask them.

72
00:07:37,061 --> 00:07:38,162
Mogi.

73
00:07:39,130 --> 00:07:40,798
Why choose a place like this?

74
00:07:44,502 --> 00:07:47,738
Probably thought dying at home
or the restaurant would cause trouble.

75
00:07:58,316 --> 00:08:00,117
Was it all a lie?

76
00:08:04,088 --> 00:08:08,092
I thought at least Mogi was on our side.

77
00:08:22,006 --> 00:08:23,274
That's enough.

78
00:08:28,179 --> 00:08:29,847
I'll take care of the rest.

79
00:08:37,922 --> 00:08:38,990
Okay.

80
00:08:39,991 --> 00:08:41,392
I'll do all I can.

81
00:08:43,928 --> 00:08:47,798
Sorry for causing you all this trouble.

82
00:09:04,348 --> 00:09:05,816
I took my annual leave,

83
00:09:06,817 --> 00:09:08,352
so I'll be off for a while.

84
00:09:24,635 --> 00:09:25,636
Excuse me.

85
00:09:26,270 --> 00:09:28,572
I have spoken to the bereaved family.

86
00:09:28,639 --> 00:09:31,142
Here are the personal effects
of Yukiteru Mogi.

87
00:09:33,411 --> 00:09:34,845
Thank you very much.

88
00:10:19,490 --> 00:10:20,591
Got a moment?

89
00:10:22,660 --> 00:10:23,828
Unlock this for me.

90
00:10:24,829 --> 00:10:25,763
Whose is this?

91
00:10:26,363 --> 00:10:27,465
Mogi's.

92
00:10:29,667 --> 00:10:31,202
I want to use this number.

93
00:10:33,337 --> 00:10:36,107
In that case,
you don't even need to unlock it.

94
00:10:37,641 --> 00:10:39,777
It's like changing to a new phone.

95
00:10:40,911 --> 00:10:41,979
Thank you.

96
00:10:43,714 --> 00:10:46,250
I think you'll only have one chance.

97
00:10:48,352 --> 00:10:49,386
I know.

98
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:06,504
FUMI

99
00:11:08,472 --> 00:11:09,807
<i>Mogi?</i>

100
00:11:10,574 --> 00:11:13,544
<i>I'm sorry. I'm a bit busy right now.</i>

101
00:11:14,145 --> 00:11:15,613
<i>Did something happen?</i>

102
00:11:20,985 --> 00:11:22,086
<i>Mogi?</i>

103
00:11:28,159 --> 00:11:29,460
<i>Hello?</i>

104
00:11:32,296 --> 00:11:33,798
Mogi is dead.

105
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:36,834
What?

106
00:11:38,469 --> 00:11:40,538
He took his own life.

107
00:11:44,208 --> 00:11:45,342
<i>Mogi was…</i>

108
00:11:48,412 --> 00:11:50,114
someone precious

109
00:11:52,183 --> 00:11:53,684
to Minoru.

110
00:11:58,355 --> 00:12:00,157
It's thanks to him being there…

111
00:12:02,493 --> 00:12:04,094
that Minoru made it this far.

112
00:12:10,835 --> 00:12:11,936
Please.

113
00:12:15,472 --> 00:12:16,707
Stop it already.

114
00:12:20,978 --> 00:12:22,413
<i>Please don't hurt…</i>

115
00:12:25,082 --> 00:12:27,318
my brother any further.

116
00:12:35,025 --> 00:12:36,393
I'm sorry.

117
00:12:39,396 --> 00:12:40,764
I'm sorry.

118
00:12:43,334 --> 00:12:45,236
<i>Please tell me what happened.</i>

119
00:12:49,573 --> 00:12:51,141
Why did my parents

120
00:12:52,676 --> 00:12:54,678
have to be killed?

121
00:12:59,283 --> 00:13:00,818
If I don't know anything,

122
00:13:03,354 --> 00:13:05,289
the pain just never goes away.

123
00:13:15,532 --> 00:13:17,735
It's all my fault.

124
00:13:21,105 --> 00:13:23,073
Because of me, he…

125
00:13:27,912 --> 00:13:29,280
1993

126
00:13:30,915 --> 00:13:34,318
When she fell from the mountain,
she struck her head and back hard,

127
00:13:34,385 --> 00:13:37,655
causing damage to her
lumbar spinal cord and brainstem.

128
00:13:37,721 --> 00:13:40,624
<i>She is stable now,</i>
<i>but if things get worse,</i>

129
00:13:40,691 --> 00:13:42,893
<i>it could be life-threatening.</i>

130
00:13:43,694 --> 00:13:46,063
Is there no way to make her better?

131
00:13:46,130 --> 00:13:49,533
To treat her, we would need
cutting-edge overseas equipment

132
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:51,902
and highly skilled surgeons.

133
00:13:51,969 --> 00:13:53,070
Then…

134
00:13:53,704 --> 00:13:55,472
what if she has surgery abroad?

135
00:13:55,539 --> 00:13:59,343
The cost would likely be extremely high.

136
00:14:03,047 --> 00:14:04,982
1995, APRIL 13

137
00:14:11,388 --> 00:14:12,523
Oh, hey.

138
00:14:12,589 --> 00:14:14,058
Were you still working?

139
00:14:14,124 --> 00:14:15,859
Sakutaro, what's wrong?

140
00:14:16,493 --> 00:14:20,297
I forgot the robot I made for my kid,
so Makoto made me go get it.

141
00:14:24,234 --> 00:14:26,804
Sadao, why are you here at this hour?

142
00:14:27,738 --> 00:14:30,107
Some urgent work came in, you know…

143
00:14:30,174 --> 00:14:31,308
I see.

144
00:14:37,381 --> 00:14:39,016
-Are you all right?
-Fumi!

145
00:14:39,817 --> 00:14:41,318
-Call an ambulance.
-Yes.

146
00:14:41,385 --> 00:14:42,720
I'm fine.

147
00:14:42,786 --> 00:14:44,254
I just need to lie down.

148
00:14:45,556 --> 00:14:48,726
Sakutaro, look after Fumi.

149
00:14:49,326 --> 00:14:50,160
What?

150
00:14:50,227 --> 00:14:52,262
I have to deliver them before 10 p.m.!

151
00:14:52,329 --> 00:14:54,732
Then, I'll deliver them for you.

152
00:14:54,798 --> 00:14:55,733
No, I have to do it.

153
00:14:55,799 --> 00:14:57,334
How can you say that now?

154
00:14:58,469 --> 00:15:01,305
Sadao, please stay by her side.

155
00:15:45,716 --> 00:15:50,587
<i>That's when Sakutaro saw the guns.</i>

156
00:15:52,790 --> 00:15:54,191
Then, my dad…

157
00:15:56,593 --> 00:15:58,328
What did he do with the guns?

158
00:15:58,395 --> 00:15:59,963
FUMI

159
00:16:00,030 --> 00:16:02,066
<i>Sakutaro, he…</i>

160
00:16:03,233 --> 00:16:04,201
Fumi?

161
00:16:04,701 --> 00:16:05,736
Fumi!

162
00:16:08,972 --> 00:16:13,210
<i>-The number you dialed cannot be reached…</i>
-It's no use.

163
00:16:13,877 --> 00:16:15,946
Maybe Mr. Koike found out.

164
00:16:16,013 --> 00:16:18,449
What happened to my father after that?

165
00:16:19,216 --> 00:16:21,452
I'll try to look for Fumi.

166
00:16:21,952 --> 00:16:23,921
I'll go ask people too.

167
00:16:51,215 --> 00:16:52,816
Buy this from me.

168
00:16:54,918 --> 00:16:57,121
But, this is…

169
00:16:57,187 --> 00:16:59,523
-I gifted it to you--
-I'll buy it back someday.

170
00:17:03,227 --> 00:17:05,462
I don't know
if I'll still have the shop then.

171
00:17:31,522 --> 00:17:32,856
Hello, sir.

172
00:17:36,760 --> 00:17:38,395
-Mr. Koike.
-Yes?

173
00:17:39,062 --> 00:17:40,397
Do you have a moment?

174
00:17:41,632 --> 00:17:43,467
This is about Tagusari, isn't it?

175
00:17:44,401 --> 00:17:45,335
What?

176
00:17:46,904 --> 00:17:50,774
According to the chief,
he won't be back for a while.

177
00:17:52,109 --> 00:17:54,845
Until then, Ishizaka and I
will support you.

178
00:17:54,912 --> 00:17:58,982
When you were in the First Division
you were in charge of that case, right?

179
00:18:01,251 --> 00:18:04,454
The Tagusari family murder 31 years ago.

180
00:18:09,059 --> 00:18:11,728
Mr. Tagusari once told me…

181
00:18:11,795 --> 00:18:14,097
If your own family was murdered,

182
00:18:14,798 --> 00:18:17,434
and the killer was in front of you,
what would you do?

183
00:18:17,935 --> 00:18:19,636
What if they were laughing,

184
00:18:21,238 --> 00:18:23,273
without ever having made amends?

185
00:18:23,340 --> 00:18:24,675
Of course, I would arrest them.

186
00:18:25,676 --> 00:18:27,778
Because that is our job.

187
00:18:31,515 --> 00:18:33,317
And what does that solve?

188
00:18:34,518 --> 00:18:39,456
How does Mr. Tagusari intend to end this?

189
00:18:42,059 --> 00:18:43,927
-Could he be planning reven--
-Kudo.

190
00:18:52,302 --> 00:18:54,271
Stay out of this.

191
00:19:36,179 --> 00:19:37,014
Kudo.

192
00:19:37,514 --> 00:19:39,616
Haruko isn't here, you know.

193
00:19:41,184 --> 00:19:43,620
I just saw her at our station
a moment ago.

194
00:19:45,389 --> 00:19:48,792
<i>Seems Public Safety arrested her</i>
<i>on suspicion of illegal operations.</i>

195
00:19:54,631 --> 00:19:56,300
How about next week or something?

196
00:19:58,869 --> 00:20:01,004
You promised
you would get a drink with me.

197
00:20:02,873 --> 00:20:04,875
I found a really great place.

198
00:20:08,178 --> 00:20:11,448
-Sorry, I have something I must do.
-What's that "something"?

199
00:20:14,017 --> 00:20:15,619
If you can't even talk about it,

200
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:17,721
then please don't do it.

201
00:20:21,191 --> 00:20:22,726
Even if the statute has expired,

202
00:20:23,293 --> 00:20:25,929
if you expose the crime,
the guilt remains in society.

203
00:20:25,996 --> 00:20:28,065
The public will judge the culprit for you!

204
00:20:38,575 --> 00:20:40,344
How many people still remember

205
00:20:42,245 --> 00:20:43,980
the cases from last year?

206
00:20:48,785 --> 00:20:50,587
Without the law's judgment…

207
00:20:52,923 --> 00:20:54,458
the bereaved never find peace.

208
00:21:32,662 --> 00:21:36,900
COVO REVERIO AOI

209
00:21:48,879 --> 00:21:50,013
I'm home.

210
00:21:57,354 --> 00:21:58,488
Great timing.

211
00:22:05,395 --> 00:22:06,530
Eat up.

212
00:22:09,866 --> 00:22:11,301
Before it gets cold.

213
00:22:31,388 --> 00:22:32,589
Is this…

214
00:22:34,291 --> 00:22:35,559
I made it.

215
00:22:36,993 --> 00:22:37,894
What?

216
00:22:42,466 --> 00:22:46,002
Mogi wrote down the recipe for us.

217
00:22:48,939 --> 00:22:50,740
FRIED RICE
INGREDIENTS / STEPS

218
00:22:50,807 --> 00:22:54,044
I think he wanted to leave the taste
of Mom's cooking behind for us.

219
00:22:59,449 --> 00:23:01,117
Back in elementary school…

220
00:23:03,587 --> 00:23:07,424
I stopped going for a while, remember?

221
00:23:12,429 --> 00:23:15,031
Everyone was staring at you, after all.

222
00:23:16,633 --> 00:23:18,602
Every morning after you went to school,

223
00:23:19,936 --> 00:23:23,707
Mogi would come over to our house.

224
00:23:26,376 --> 00:23:27,444
He did?

225
00:23:29,846 --> 00:23:32,616
He probably didn't really know
how to cheer me up.

226
00:23:34,284 --> 00:23:37,888
But, until it was time to open his shop,
he didn't really do anything,

227
00:23:39,222 --> 00:23:41,124
just stayed by my side the whole time.

228
00:23:43,760 --> 00:23:44,861
And then,

229
00:23:45,929 --> 00:23:48,131
when I told him,
"I'm going to school today,"

230
00:23:49,266 --> 00:23:52,602
he saw me off at the front door.

231
00:23:55,906 --> 00:23:56,973
Then…

232
00:23:59,442 --> 00:24:04,180
he kept following behind me while waving.

233
00:24:05,682 --> 00:24:07,651
All the way to the school gates.

234
00:24:13,323 --> 00:24:15,225
When I walked through the gates,

235
00:24:18,628 --> 00:24:19,863
Mogi…

236
00:24:22,532 --> 00:24:24,301
was crying tears of joy.

237
00:24:38,081 --> 00:24:39,015
I…

238
00:24:42,018 --> 00:24:43,286
I can't do it after all.

239
00:24:48,024 --> 00:24:50,727
No matter what, I just can't hate him.

240
00:24:59,402 --> 00:25:02,005
I have no right to face
Mom and Dad like this, do I?

241
00:25:16,686 --> 00:25:17,821
I…

242
00:25:22,859 --> 00:25:25,128
have no intention of forgiving him.

243
00:25:28,431 --> 00:25:30,634
There's no changing what he did,

244
00:25:34,004 --> 00:25:36,272
and he deceived us this whole time.

245
00:25:42,212 --> 00:25:43,213
But…

246
00:26:01,798 --> 00:26:03,600
Mogi is on our side.

247
00:26:56,019 --> 00:26:59,989
Our winter jackets and such
are still left at the dry cleaners, right?

248
00:27:03,493 --> 00:27:05,028
What should we do about them?

249
00:27:06,596 --> 00:27:07,831
Just leave them.

250
00:27:10,033 --> 00:27:11,468
We won't be wearing them.

251
00:27:22,579 --> 00:27:23,680
True.

252
00:27:26,616 --> 00:27:28,518
Is that what we should talk about now?

253
00:27:30,754 --> 00:27:31,855
No, it isn't.

254
00:27:42,332 --> 00:27:44,400
What will you do when this is all over?

255
00:27:47,370 --> 00:27:49,239
I hadn't really asked you yet.

256
00:27:54,277 --> 00:27:55,512
What are you going to do?

257
00:28:05,522 --> 00:28:07,223
I don't want to be alone.

258
00:28:12,128 --> 00:28:14,130
Please spare me from that at least.

259
00:28:23,339 --> 00:28:25,108
MIZOGUCHI TSUTSUI LAW FIRM

260
00:28:25,175 --> 00:28:26,476
<i>Mr. Mizoguchi,</i>

261
00:28:26,543 --> 00:28:29,145
I hear you provide support
for organizations

262
00:28:29,212 --> 00:28:31,114
for the families of murder victims.

263
00:28:32,215 --> 00:28:34,951
Please tell me about
the bereaved families of cases

264
00:28:35,018 --> 00:28:37,220
where the statute
of limitations has expired.

265
00:28:43,159 --> 00:28:44,527
<i>That case…</i>

266
00:28:44,594 --> 00:28:46,496
isn't over yet.

267
00:28:49,032 --> 00:28:51,134
I am equally guilty.

268
00:28:54,571 --> 00:28:55,939
Mr. Sasaoka,

269
00:28:56,573 --> 00:28:58,208
how are you going to end this?

270
00:29:00,743 --> 00:29:02,846
Are you going to keep running away?

271
00:29:03,746 --> 00:29:04,814
<i>Or…</i>

272
00:29:29,672 --> 00:29:31,274
How did you find this place?

273
00:29:31,774 --> 00:29:34,844
Why do you think we joined the police?

274
00:29:37,213 --> 00:29:38,681
We won't let you get away.

275
00:29:54,898 --> 00:29:56,399
I'll tell you everything.

276
00:29:59,502 --> 00:30:01,237
About what happened back then.

277
00:30:04,274 --> 00:30:05,375
No.

278
00:30:06,409 --> 00:30:07,777
I'll ask him directly.

279
00:30:14,217 --> 00:30:15,752
You know who we are, don't you?

280
00:30:17,487 --> 00:30:19,088
We're the Tagusari brothers.

281
00:30:19,155 --> 00:30:22,125
The sons of Sakutaro and Yuka Tagusari.

282
00:30:30,300 --> 00:30:32,168
Why don't you say something?

283
00:30:33,303 --> 00:30:36,339
We are the sons of the people
you had Mogi kill.

284
00:30:40,009 --> 00:30:41,811
Have you ever thought about it?

285
00:30:44,380 --> 00:30:46,416
How we lived our lives

286
00:30:47,817 --> 00:30:49,419
these past 31 years?

287
00:30:52,956 --> 00:30:54,324
That day,

288
00:30:56,025 --> 00:30:57,860
our parents died,

289
00:30:59,128 --> 00:31:02,565
and the statute expired without us
knowing why they were killed.

290
00:31:05,201 --> 00:31:07,737
We didn't know how we were
supposed to keep living.

291
00:31:12,809 --> 00:31:17,413
Getting revenge on you
was our only reason to stay alive.

292
00:31:21,617 --> 00:31:23,119
Hey, say something!

293
00:31:23,853 --> 00:31:25,788
You set the whole thing up, didn't you?

294
00:31:25,855 --> 00:31:29,492
You used Mogi's mother
to make him kill my parents!

295
00:31:29,559 --> 00:31:31,394
Stop it!

296
00:31:32,095 --> 00:31:33,596
He doesn't remember.

297
00:31:34,597 --> 00:31:36,265
He also doesn't know

298
00:31:37,300 --> 00:31:39,002
anything about you two.

299
00:31:45,041 --> 00:31:46,175
He is sick.

300
00:31:51,514 --> 00:31:53,716
He doesn't understand what he did,

301
00:31:55,118 --> 00:31:57,653
nor the meaning behind your revenge.

302
00:32:00,156 --> 00:32:01,824
He knows nothing.

303
00:32:22,545 --> 00:32:28,418
<i>That night, Sakutaro found out</i>
<i>about the gun manufacturing.</i>

304
00:32:28,484 --> 00:32:31,521
1995, APRIL 13

305
00:32:37,393 --> 00:32:38,694
What is this?

306
00:32:40,630 --> 00:32:42,632
Why did you make these?

307
00:32:44,333 --> 00:32:45,368
Sadao!

308
00:32:47,870 --> 00:32:49,672
I need money

309
00:32:51,441 --> 00:32:52,642
for Fumi's surgery.

310
00:32:58,247 --> 00:33:00,183
Please pretend you didn't see this.

311
00:33:02,218 --> 00:33:03,386
I'm begging you!

312
00:33:24,807 --> 00:33:26,275
I'm sorry.

313
00:33:29,679 --> 00:33:34,117
I'm not exactly a great person myself.

314
00:33:36,018 --> 00:33:39,422
But I don't want to be
a father who is in the wrong.

315
00:33:40,623 --> 00:33:42,391
I want to be a father

316
00:33:43,593 --> 00:33:46,696
that Makoto and Minoru can be proud of.

317
00:33:50,967 --> 00:33:54,070
Sadao, please turn yourself in.

318
00:33:54,770 --> 00:33:58,274
I'll look after this factory
until you come back!

319
00:34:00,476 --> 00:34:01,711
Sadao!

320
00:34:12,955 --> 00:34:15,258
If you can't do that,

321
00:34:19,562 --> 00:34:21,430
I will take this gun to the police.

322
00:34:25,701 --> 00:34:28,337
<i>The guns were being</i>
<i>traded offshore, weren't they?</i>

323
00:34:28,905 --> 00:34:32,108
They were transported from a warehouse
by a large fishing boat.

324
00:34:33,676 --> 00:34:35,011
But that day,

325
00:34:35,878 --> 00:34:40,283
because Sakutaro took a gun
home with him, the deal was called off…

326
00:34:42,852 --> 00:34:44,453
What time is it now?

327
00:34:46,289 --> 00:34:50,259
I did something terrible to Koji.
I have to hurry and apologize.

328
00:34:50,326 --> 00:34:51,427
It's okay.

329
00:34:51,494 --> 00:34:52,728
It's okay.

330
00:34:53,896 --> 00:34:57,867
That fisherman named Koji,

331
00:35:00,703 --> 00:35:02,505
was killed.

332
00:35:03,906 --> 00:35:05,641
Driven into a corner,

333
00:35:06,475 --> 00:35:09,579
my husband sought help from Mr. Sasaoka
of the Prefectural Police.

334
00:35:10,279 --> 00:35:12,315
The Igarashi-gumi
has been threatening you?

335
00:35:12,381 --> 00:35:13,516
GET LOST ALREADY

336
00:35:13,583 --> 00:35:17,453
Mom says she will never
hand over this place,

337
00:35:18,321 --> 00:35:20,590
and she won't listen no matter what I say.

338
00:35:21,490 --> 00:35:23,492
Is this place
really that important to her?

339
00:35:24,227 --> 00:35:25,328
I think…

340
00:35:27,096 --> 00:35:28,631
it's for my sake.

341
00:35:29,198 --> 00:35:32,702
This shop is the only place I can work.

342
00:35:35,871 --> 00:35:39,508
Mr. Mogi, you know
Mr. Kaga from the tatami shop?

343
00:35:41,077 --> 00:35:43,312
The Igarashi-gumi killed him.

344
00:35:45,047 --> 00:35:46,215
Next is…

345
00:35:47,383 --> 00:35:49,018
my mom?

346
00:35:55,691 --> 00:35:57,059
I'm begging you.

347
00:36:00,696 --> 00:36:02,031
Please help me.

348
00:36:06,535 --> 00:36:09,138
I'll go talk with the Igarashi-gumi.

349
00:36:10,506 --> 00:36:11,807
Really?

350
00:36:13,509 --> 00:36:17,213
In exchange,
why don't you help me out a bit?

351
00:36:22,885 --> 00:36:27,056
I want you to get rid of that family.

352
00:36:29,659 --> 00:36:32,828
What do you mean "get rid of"?

353
00:36:34,597 --> 00:36:36,098
The Tagusari family…

354
00:36:37,733 --> 00:36:39,268
Kill them all for me.

355
00:36:41,971 --> 00:36:45,941
That's how you backed him into a corner.

356
00:36:46,876 --> 00:36:49,945
You probably figured Mogi
would do whatever he was told.

357
00:36:52,581 --> 00:36:54,550
Mogi is easy to deceive.

358
00:36:57,520 --> 00:36:59,155
Because he is kind.

359
00:37:05,928 --> 00:37:07,930
Accepting the terms of the deal,

360
00:37:10,132 --> 00:37:11,701
Mogi then…

361
00:37:14,937 --> 00:37:18,674
1995, APRIL 26

362
00:37:18,741 --> 00:37:21,210
I'll cause a short circuit in ten minutes.

363
00:37:28,984 --> 00:37:29,952
Ready?

364
00:37:33,222 --> 00:37:34,390
Mogi!

365
00:37:59,682 --> 00:38:02,785
KARASHIMA METAL FACTORY

366
00:38:42,525 --> 00:38:44,894
Paramedics! Over here!

367
00:38:46,529 --> 00:38:48,097
We found someone!

368
00:38:49,532 --> 00:38:50,699
<i>In the end,</i>

369
00:38:51,634 --> 00:38:55,938
with the fire insurance
and the money from selling the land,

370
00:38:59,508 --> 00:39:01,544
I was able to have my surgery.

371
00:39:10,219 --> 00:39:12,455
I was able to walk again

372
00:39:14,623 --> 00:39:15,891
and even started working--

373
00:39:15,958 --> 00:39:17,460
How did it feel?

374
00:39:21,430 --> 00:39:23,833
Climbing mountains with that money.

375
00:39:32,341 --> 00:39:34,043
It felt like a dream.

376
00:39:43,285 --> 00:39:45,321
Because I didn't know anything.

377
00:39:48,557 --> 00:39:51,460
<i>Around the time my work</i>
<i>finally started getting on track,</i>

378
00:39:52,194 --> 00:39:53,929
<i>I heard the truth.</i>

379
00:39:53,996 --> 00:39:55,197
Sadao.

380
00:39:56,565 --> 00:39:57,900
I can't do this anymore.

381
00:40:01,136 --> 00:40:03,372
Please, look at this.

382
00:40:04,306 --> 00:40:05,374
I got it from Minoru.

383
00:40:06,909 --> 00:40:09,912
His school will have a parents' day,
and he wants me to come!

384
00:40:11,981 --> 00:40:13,415
He wants me!

385
00:40:15,251 --> 00:40:16,418
Sadao!

386
00:40:17,753 --> 00:40:19,188
I'm begging you!

387
00:40:21,991 --> 00:40:24,693
Please let me turn myself in!

388
00:40:31,534 --> 00:40:33,602
What will happen to your mother then?

389
00:40:34,470 --> 00:40:35,437
What?

390
00:40:36,171 --> 00:40:38,741
If she finds out her son is a murderer.

391
00:40:39,308 --> 00:40:40,976
B-But…

392
00:40:41,043 --> 00:40:43,946
If we stay quiet, no one gets hurt.

393
00:40:45,714 --> 00:40:47,082
It's for everyone's sake.

394
00:40:48,250 --> 00:40:49,552
You understand, don't you?

395
00:40:52,154 --> 00:40:53,088
Dear.

396
00:40:58,127 --> 00:41:00,963
What are you talking about?

397
00:41:03,566 --> 00:41:07,303
<i>Mogi regretted it the entire time.</i>

398
00:41:08,971 --> 00:41:10,172
If only back then,

399
00:41:11,140 --> 00:41:12,708
I had stopped him…

400
00:41:12,775 --> 00:41:13,809
That's enough.

401
00:41:18,314 --> 00:41:19,882
I heard what I wanted to know.

402
00:41:19,949 --> 00:41:22,051
Wait, I'm still talking--

403
00:41:22,117 --> 00:41:23,986
I've waited 31 years.

404
00:41:27,189 --> 00:41:28,691
That's more than enough.

405
00:42:26,849 --> 00:42:31,120
KANAGAWA PREFECTURE POLICE

406
00:42:42,297 --> 00:42:44,933
Isn't it about time you tell the truth?

407
00:42:45,834 --> 00:42:47,136
Mr. Koike.

408
00:42:49,705 --> 00:42:51,507
I should be asking you that!

409
00:42:53,509 --> 00:42:55,511
Haruko Ashikaga.

410
00:43:00,549 --> 00:43:03,819
Just what on earth are you hiding?

411
00:43:21,370 --> 00:43:22,604
Mogi.

412
00:43:27,876 --> 00:43:29,011
Makoto.

413
00:43:29,878 --> 00:43:30,946
Let me kill him!

414
00:43:46,595 --> 00:43:48,030
<i>Hey, Minoru.</i>

415
00:43:48,997 --> 00:43:51,366
<i>What do you want to be when you grow up?</i>

416
00:43:51,934 --> 00:43:53,602
<i>We've found the killer.</i>

417
00:43:54,369 --> 00:43:56,538
<i>I'm glad you're my brother, Makoto.</i>

418
00:43:56,605 --> 00:43:57,573
Subtitle translation by: Nix S.

